Bandits have reportedly attacked Sabon Layi community in Birnin-Gwari Local Government Area of Kaduna State, killing three people and abducted several others. A community leader, Anas Musa who confirmed the attack to Channels Television on Friday said the bandits stormed Sabon Layi village at about 12pm on Thursday and started shooting sporadically. The community leader disclosed that the bandits killed three farmers in the process, namely Anas Sabonlayi, Abubakar Dankibiya, and Harisu Un-Guwar Lemu. The Chairman of Birnin Gwari Emirate Progressive Union (BEPU), Usman Kasai, also confirmed the attack, saying they are trying to ascertain the exact number of those kidnapped and still with the bandits inside the forest.